\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Now first of all can you tell me the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1905}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}
{\xmlattrvalue 2}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}}April the 2nd, 1905{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Gravesend{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}Kent{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you tell me the neighbourhood, describe the neighbourhood of round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I should like to describe it as a middle class neighbourhood. Medium size houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Detached or terraced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I can't remember now, but its either semi-detached or detached, probably semi-detached.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And how far away were streets where, say, poorer people lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I should say two or three hundred yards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did poor children sort of play in the streets and where the middle class children
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There was still quite a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4480363\charrsid1014503 residential}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  segregation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 This was, well it was a semi main road really. And the poorer neighbourhood would be terraced houses where traffic wouldn't go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What was your own house like, can you describe, you know, in some detail, the rooms, the size of the rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Um, well now, I can't remember the first house, where I was born, you see because we were only there, in my life about,
 I suppose, a couple of years, three years, something like that. Then we went on to another one, another house, only a few hundred yards away, in a similar type of road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you were there until when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I should think until I was about 8, 7 or 8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Then you moved again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Then we moved into a larger house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5266015\charrsid1014503 Still in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 ravesend{\*\xmlclose}
 in the same sort of area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, this was, oh I should think a couple of miles away from the town. In fact it was really country, it was the last, my father b
ought a plot and built this house, the last one in the built up area. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5266015\charrsid1014503 Housin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 g council house property, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Perhaps it would be better to describe that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That was the one I can remember. That was definitely a larger house, semi-detached because my father built it for \'85
 so that he could house somebody else next door, a couple of spinsters. Oh, well now look -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Let's start on the ground floor, can you remember anything of the plan of the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well we had a very large dining room, whi
ch could be divided off, because my father was, had meetings, he used to have a Bible Class on a Sunday, so that it was built specially so that it could contain about twenty people you see. That was the room in which we had our meals. There was a sitting 
room, very seldom used. A kitchen. Quite large. And scullery. And lavatory down - stairs. That was the downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Now how many bedrooms were there - one, two, three, four bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about servants bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and then, that was another storey upstairs. Two storeys. A sort of attic storey, you s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5266015\charrsid1014503 ee storey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  roofs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How many servants did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We had two servants resident. One elderly woman and one younger one which also acted as, I think she acted as nursemaid partly too. Th
en my mother used to be fully working the whole time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Your mother was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. There was no sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Being waited on hand and foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. We were waited on at table you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 By the younger or the older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh the younger one. The older cook was always kept in the kitchen, got up at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past six{\*\xmlclose} in the morning, to do the stove.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What did she do after that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well she cooked the breakfast. I mean that was her domain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, she was always in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and I was always teasing her!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your mother do any cooking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I don't think she did. I mean she would do the sort of, preserving the fruit and all that sort of thing. I suppose she must have - I don't think she did much at all as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember her making a cup of tea, or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, we had a regular set tea you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. And what - can you remember something of the other servant, her duties - what she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well they both had to get up at the same time. I remember that there was cleaning and er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember her looking after you and doing things for you personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We had quite a lot of changes of the younger one. And I can remember the ones who looked after me, the 
ones I liked, you see. And they'd take me and my sister out for walks and I mean we weren't to a large extent allowed to go out much on one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5266015\charrsid1014503 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 s own at all. I am talking up to the age of when I went out, away to school, daily you see. Then of course - I was to a certain extent independent
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You would go on your own to school would you Or would somebody accompany you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no. Well now, when we start there, the first time I went to school was at five. And I think we were taken to school to start with. I
t was a very short walk. And then I can remember, I might have been six then. And we had to go on our own and definitely told to keep to the pavements, and I can remember jumping over the lines without touching, and all the way to school
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your mother, did she spend quite a lot of time with you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. I mean she always bathed us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She did. Would she get you up in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you eat all your meals with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we ha
d except of course when I was at school, and that was two miles away, and I used to come home for lunch. And well it wasn't a convenient time, so I used to have my lunch on my own then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You didn't have a separate nursery really, you were with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, always. All through yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And so, would she be more a housemaid usually than a Nanny, this younger girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You know, I have just got a feeling she might have had somebody in occasionally to take us out, probably an additional one, f
rom time to time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, to take you for walks and that sort of thing. But the main kind of care, and teaching you, you know, how to behave, was your mother?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was my mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about your father, how much did he do in the home in the way of things like repairs, helping -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well he would domineer. I mean even the meals, my mother always asked him "What shall we have tomorrow?" and he would - he was the king pin of the family, my mother worshipped him you see, and my father dictated ev
erybody about. But in such a way that he was popular, you know, he did it in quite a nice way. But I mean his law was final.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would he even have given the servants orders, or did that go through your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That went through my mother. Of course we had a gardener as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we haven't talked about outdoors. So would she also tell the gardener what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, my mother had nothing to do with the gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. And questions like how the rooms were to be furnished, or any change of the rooms, were those all referred to him too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Everything in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you think of anything which she would - what about clothing - the clothes that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, my mother would do all the buying for the children hersel
f. I mean she wasn't at all, her own taste wasn't at all, conscious of dress conscious at all. But we were kept in, she was always changing our clothes and, which I hated, I mean I was always glad to have the old clothes. I mean I can remember some awful 
crying, upset when I was told to put a new hat on, and new shoes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Did she take you with her, did you have a choice in what new things were bought, or did she decide for you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, she decided and I didn't like them very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what about Pauline, did she sort of consult her in what she should wear? Can you remember when she was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember much about my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. And your father, did she sort of buy his clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 He would do all his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about your father and you, how much time did you spend with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, when he was at, because I mean the working hours were long you see .. eh ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What were his working hours actually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well he would go off, we always had family prayers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Every day, yes. With the servants coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well breakfast was at eight, and I suppose this would be immediately afterwards then he would get off to business about nine you see
. And he'd come back for lunch. And then, er, I mean I can't remember the earliest days, probably he went back sooner, but later I mean he wouldn't go back until about three, you see. And then he would come back in the evening about at the early part of t
he week about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past six{\*\xmlclose}, and then later in the week, Fridays it would be about 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past eight{\*\xmlclose} and about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past nine{\*\xmlclose} on Saturday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 He worked a full day on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Then he would come home for tea then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I see, he would have two breaks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, a short tea break. Despite the two miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, he, in that last house we were talking about, he cycled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 He cycled, yes. But you know, given that he was away so much of the week and Saturday, did you see anythin
g of him to talk to? Or feel his sort of interest at all \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well I would feel his influence was definitely, there, I mean we always went out together on a Wednesday afternoon, used to have a trap (?) or something like that, and the whole lot of us would go out, and we looked forward to it, the time he was with us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What would you do on one of those excursions?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we would just take a tray and go out five or six miles and have tea at a village and come back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, did you look at anything, you know, churches and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It was just an outing together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I suppose his interest was more on gardens and flowers. And of course he was a keen photographer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you find him easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 In the early days yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How do you mean by the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well, I mean when I got up to my teens, probably it would be different, but um, I mean he was full of fun and play and as far as I was concerned I mean I enjoyed his company much more than my mother's. Who was probably stricter with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he ask you, did he take an interest in your friends at all was he interested in your social life outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not really no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not fussy about who you were friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well yes. I think this rather
, I don't know about what he felt, but I think my mother was very protective and over protective and kept us rather to the home too much, that was one of my troubles, not making many friends. I mean we didn't have parties at home. And we went out to one o
r two but they dwindled out because they we reciprocated.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You never had birthday parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we would have it on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you wouldn't have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Very seldom I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Why do you think that was, why did she have that attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Her own she had a very limited range of friends herself, think that would probably be the reason for that. Her whole life was a religious one, she sent an enormous lot of time with poorer people and helping people, and her interests were, you 
see this mission which they went to, the people who came there were all poor, except for our family and perhaps two others, of a similar class, and I was rather brought up in that atmosphere. Until I went to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}County{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} after eight, then I had a grea
t friend who lived opposite you see, we spent a lot of time together. And I made friends there but it was not much in going to their houses, it was largely a friendship at school and sort of walking home together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So it was more that she was taken up 
with other interests, and good works, than it was any feeling that you should be kept apart from other children because they might contaminate you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think she had that too. I think she was afraid of the influence of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 In a religious way rather than in a snobbish way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh definitely not in a snobbish way, no, no, no. She was very nervous in a c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5266015\charrsid1014503 
lass above herself, you see my f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 ather's side were a step up from her and of course we used to go there once or twice a year and I knew that this was very strange to her, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you sense this or did she actually say so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I sensed it later, and she said so too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What was her own father and mother's social -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well he was started off as a carpenter, and then he made good in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bournemouth{\*\xmlclose}
 as a builder, and did very well on that with a fairly large family, and they lived very comfortably, at the time my mother was married. Another point was you see my mother was a semi-invalid with asthma, and she was restricted to her own house and ha
d I think very little education, and I think this had some effect on her difficulty to mix with people. This has come out in my sister too you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Um -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were asking about punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, that's true. Can you remember something of
 your parents ideas really of how children ought to be brought up, what part 'em and punishment played in this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I mean they were strict, I mean when they said such and such a thing must be done, I mean we had to do it. When we kicked against th
e traces, well that could happen, I suppose it must have during the earlier period, but I mean we did accept that in the period of my remembrance. I can remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did it have to be done immediately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I will tell you what - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not the sort of "Yes - later" and a lot of argument -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes. I mean we were given a lot of freedom and when things were - I mean I think that it was pretty reasonable but I can remember the sort of moral training on lies and what not you see. I remember break
ing some tool of my father's and he giving me a lecture and "Now Norris, I am sending you up to your room" that was the punishment we had you see. "I am not sending you up to your room because you have broken the tool, but because you told me a lie and yo
u
 said you didn't break it." And then I can remember about a week later that something else happened you see, I can't remember whether I had broken something, or something of that nature, and I owned up right away. "Off you go to your room Norris!" And I j
ust couldn't understand it!. I had told the truth and I still got the same punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you expostulate at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I did, I did. And I don't think I got it on the second time. I suppose he was annoyed at the time. But I never, all my life at the
 time I didn't have any spontaneous corporal punishment at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have any at all of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes, the one form of punishment which my mother gave, "If you do this smack your bottom"! you see. And this would always wait until you were in your bath. But it was in such a way that it didn't worry us very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would that happen quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well not really, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you never had a jolly good hiding \'85in quites
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Never, no. I was never slapped by either parent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think that it was a principle, a thought out principle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think it was, yes. I mean we had it at school you see. But not at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And from what you can remember of your friends, do you think they would have had more in the way of hidings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But the punishment was to be sent to your room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well either in the corner, and if that didn't work, up you go to your room! And that seemed to take the effervescence out of me. I mean then, in a few minutes "Can I come down father?" and you know". You stay u there" and that was all there was to it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No sort of tasks like having to weed the garden and so forth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, well not as a punishment, this was a matter of routine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You had definite jobs in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well yes. One job I had, I had to go out and collect the milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It wasn't delivered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no. Of course we wanted fresh farm milk. It wasn't far, I suppose about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname metricconverter}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 300 yards}}}300 yards{\*\xmlclose}. And of course I hated that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Why do you think you hated that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Because I had to do it every day and I wanted to do other things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh yes. I mean I think I - I did it, yes, I had to do it. And I probably grumbled and created a scene a bit sometimes. And then I had to clean t
hat wretched chicken house out. Every Saturday morning, as you know I have never kept chickens since! But I suppose I was about ten or eleven then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What else - anything in the way of indoor jobs. Anything in the way of indoor jobs. Were you suppose to
 keep your own shoes clean, that was done for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That was all done for me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was that the gardener or the maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, it would be the maid would do that. The gardener didn't come in the house. And Mother did all my clothes, kept everything 
tidy. To my regret, I mean I had no training on that may you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So you didn't, so you don't remember doing anything for yourself personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. I wasn't I was really quite dependent on my Mother on practically everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I wonder how much you remember about what Pauline had to do in the home, do you remember much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't think she did much either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember, you haven't any memories of her doing jobs in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I wasn't very close to my sister and, I think one just doesn't take much notice as a child of - well I didn't of my...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. So you don't remember much in, say, differences in the way you were treated by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I do remember that they were very fair, there was definitely no favouritis
m at all there only I was a bully a bit, and I, I always felt that she was a cry baby. Well I suppose I was doing rather the things like Stephen does, I suppose it was the natural thing. Because I was the one who got punished you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were your parents hard on you for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well it was the usual thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not to worry your sister, kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh "Up you go Norris to your room".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But she wasn't a sort of companion to you in any way, you didn't do things together with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no. We didn't No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Your father you said was out, you know, a great part of the week days. Do you remember his, besides sort of being you know, very much master of the house can you remember his doing actually doing any jobs in the house or garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh the garden. He was a keen gardener. Well the greenhouse and raising things. He was always doing something, he would never sit down. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12461324\charrsid1014503  did he teach you or Pauline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  anything do you remember? Of any kind, I mean either gardening or the Bible or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh well. On the religious side they would, both of them. I mean he would - games too. Tennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have your own court?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Croquet and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And the religious side, was that, can you describe to me how often a how he would set about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, I am just trying to - they had a Sunday School there but we weren't allowed to go because they felt they -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I suppose it was reading books, you know, on Sundays you see we were - only religious books wer
e read you see singing too you see - hymns. The whole atmosphere would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A strict Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Om.{\*\xmlclose}
 I mean there were certain things definitely taboo. You see. Anything in the way of what was considered work. Or unnecessary work. We never even had 
a hot dinner, we had a hot joint on a Saturday and cold on Sunday you see. I mean they felt that you shouldn't employ anybody on the Sunday, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did the servants have the day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well the old girl who was in our - had nowhere to go. She wa
s... But everything was done to lesson any work. Now I think my mother did do cooking on that day. I think, I mean they definitely went out of their way to restrict any work, yes. By having these cold meals and of course no dusting done, or anything like 
that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have to make your own bed on that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 My mother always did, always did. And if she went on a holiday, or hotel, on Sunday she would make her own bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How interesting. And things like amusements, could you play games on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. We used to go country walks. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Tennis?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, that was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about, did you have any musical instruments in the home, did they have a piano? Didn't you learn the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh my goodness yes! But that was, I suppose I was about ten when I went to piano lessons. My father played the flute, the people but er -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would that have been not done on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no that would be done. But I mean it would probably be playing hymns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he have a study at all, a sort of separate place of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, but I think every morning he had about ten minutes of reading. I don't know what he did read. On his own, sort of meditation sort of thing, before he went off. No, he didn't have a separate study. But
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I mean you didn't go to him, I am thinking of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Prince Albert
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, how he would have his children, you know say for half an hour alone, I just wondered if your father did anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, there was nothing that you could sort of say it was regular. But it was
 was rather under the influence of their life you see and anything we did, or anything, I mean one was permeated with the atmosphere of religion. But not ritual it was a non-denominational mission you see and of course anything Catholic or 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}High{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or even Anglican was frowned upon you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes. So that how you would learn about the Bible and Bible stories and this sort of thing would be more through Services and family prayers would it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I think they would read books with the Bible stories in it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did they read to you quite often I mean as an evening past-time for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I learnt to read pretty early, and then I was very keen on reading you see. And, oh yes well I remember we used to have these Peter Rabbit books and t
he thing which I looked forward to, I used to go in my parents bed in the morning, and they used to read us Peter Rabbit, or a book of that nature, yes before they go up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, just occasionally. And it was a real treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You didn't have a bed-time story, the reading was in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Can you remember when you were little, I mean, say sort of 5, 6 or 7, can you remember what bed-time was like, was it ritualised, did you have routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Timeward. I think that we went off regularly at a certain time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember when it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think it was six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. And can you sort of describe to me, we are interested in knowing how it was, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well we had a pretty good tea you see, about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past four{\*\xmlclose} or five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You, your sister and your mother together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh my father would come up you see for tea and he would go back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I see. I didn't realise he did that every day - every day he came back for tea time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Because you said on a Saturday -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Perhaps we had - I am a bit hazy on this. They had an evening meal you see, later, somewhere about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A cooked meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Generally a cooked meal Yes. But that was quite late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But tea would have been you, and your sister I suppose, and your mother, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I suppose it was. No, no, it would have been with my parents. I am still wondering whether my father did come home and go back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 If it was two miles, cycling -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I mean I did the same, and it didn't seem, looking back on it, the distance didn't seem to be so much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What time did you say that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 About five, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And then, what would you do after tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well you know I can't remember the early years, I mean later on, as soon as I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What age can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well, as soon as I could read you see, and then my Father was interested in stamps too, and I was very keen on that with him. You see, he had a collection. It is very difficult to remember the age previously
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I just wondered if you could remember any time within the period up to when you were thirteen, how the evenings might go, it doesn't remember if you can't remember the exact year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well in the summer, when I was old enough, we we
re generally playing in the garden, we were out in the garden a lot. As long as the weather was all right. And then of course there was no wireless you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about records, did you have a gramophone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would your father have thought that all right?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but he had one excursion a year to the Crystal Palace to hear the messiah on Good Friday and year after year -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You all went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes. That was his one sort of classical -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he enjoy it very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh he did. He liked the choir singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That was the only thing he would go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
You see theatre and cinemas were frowned on. And when I went to my Aunt Mary in Grantham she took us to the cinema you see, and she got ticked off for doing so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It's a bit hard isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Isn't it!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you think the Messiah was all right because it was on a religious theme, is that why he felt he could go to see it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I suppose it was really. I mean we would go to - he was very keen on exhibitions or sport too, a certain amount of sport, cricket -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember any exhibitions you went to with him or museums?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we used to go up to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Science{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}
Museum{\*\xmlclose}, and Museum and Tower of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and all those. And we had this annual holiday, we always had a fortnight away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh did you? Tell me about that, where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Every time a different place you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Seaside{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Seaside{\*\xmlclose} generally, Swanage and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Isle of Wight
{\*\xmlclose}, Bridlington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Where would you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 At rooms, they used to have. With food given. What do you call it? A boarding house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would you take any servants with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just yourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You remember doing that from when you were very small children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes I do. I mean we
 enjoyed this and they must have made it a holiday for us to enjoy to, you see. We enjoyed going on the beach. Then of course we went down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bournemouth{\*\xmlclose}
 twice a year. That was my mother's parents. There were an enormous lot of cousins there, and that was 
quite a highlight and we would go down to the beach there and mix with the cousins. That was the one family relationships we had with my Mother's people, on my Father's side there was only my Father's sister and nobody else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, that's your Aunti Ne
lly, your Father's sister? Yes. And when you went to the seaside, did you go, did you ever make friends with other families? Or did you keep to yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think that we must have kept to ourselves. My father was would have done, quite lot more. I 
am remember he met up with some fishermen, going out with them, but my mother didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
She was possessive with him too, kept him on what she felt was an even keel! I think that he would have been quite a lad if it hadn't been for her. Rather oppressive attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did she have an easy way with people of all classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Can you tell me, we are quite interested in meal times, you know, the sort of food you had and how a meal would be, say for example, well Sundays are not a good day, say a normal day, lunch when your father came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We had a good breakfast. Egg and Bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, or cereal. No, cereals weren't there. Porridge we had. And you know, all well laid on the table. Sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would they mind wait on breakfast or was that on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She would bring it in, the hot part, and that would be the end of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you would help yourselves then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have coffee and tea, or just coffee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We didn't have coffee, we had tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And, what in the way of toast and bread? Did you have toast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we had toast and bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And marmelade and honey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not honey I don't think. We had marmelade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And did you all have to be there at a set time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. And er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was a gong beaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we had a gong before, and you know if I was late I was told. And if my hair was untidy I was told off!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were all supposed to come at the same time to meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your father keep to this himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And did he start with grace, at all meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And did you have grace at the end of the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I believe we did at the beginning, and I think that dwindled off after a bit!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That interests me, why do you think it dwindled off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I don't know. I think possibly because some of us might have had a meal quickly, something like that, quite possibly we weren't all there at the end but we were definitely all there at the beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And at lunch, did you have - how many courses did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Now, wait a minute, did we? We didn't have three courses, I think we generally had two. I don't know whether we always did. Quite frequently, and then it was a regular routine this lunch. We had the joint on Saturday, it was always a sirloin of beef.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Always? The whole year through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes, well, except Christmas, you know, this long bit of bone, sort of cut down, that was hot on the Saturday, cold on Sunday, with generally a ver
y nicely made salad, with hard boiled egg on the top, always the same. And a meringue pudding. Funny how this comes back to mind, and that was always on Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Any dressing with the salad can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but I think that that was a bought one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Of the salad cream variety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And cheese, did you have cheese and pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes. My father was very fond of pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about fresh fruit, do you remember having that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. We had our own apples. Yes, plent
y of fruit. In fact my father always brought fruit home one Saturday evening from a little shop, they sold them themselves, he wanted to help this little shop and he used to go in "Two pounds, of that, a pound of that, three pounds of that" you know. And 
he would get them altogether and take them home to my mother. Then on the Monday we had the meat turned into a shepherds Pie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what did you have with it? Other vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Always two vegetables. Always two vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And always a pudding. My Mother's range was not very big.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It sounds like standard type of meals really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes. Stewed fruit and custard. And sometimes some sort of crusty puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Steamed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Steamed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And there was always cheese?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There was always cheese about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Anything, well presumably nothing alcoholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no. Strictly total.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Any beverages at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh there was squash in the house. It wasn't ad lib at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about tea and coffee, other than at breakfast. At tea I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Oh I think there was a sort of elevenses, or something that's when you could have a squash, or a biscuit or if you wanted some milk.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Could you go into the kitchen and ask the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think one would ask my mother, no I wouldn't go and help myself except for water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you wouldn't ask the cook yourself or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were telling me about the joint. You would have it as a shepherds pie on Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well that was gone by then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What would you have, say, on Tuesday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well it might be chops, or it might be, I think probably on a Tuesday we might have had fish. I mean they wouldn't have had fish on Friday because that was too -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Popish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes! Fish, boiled haddock I suppose it
 was. I don't know what it was. But it was very much but you know, there was no variety at all in the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would you have had much of a seasoning, you know, herbs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not herbs, parsley sauce, that's what we had. But I don't think there was a great deal of finesse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Very plain English food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And the tea, what was that like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh, thinly cut bread and butter. We had to have so many slices of bread and butter before we could have cake or biscuits. In fact the first bit you had to have without any jam at all!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Could you then have biscuits and cake?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 If it was a very rich sort of thing, you were allowed one, or if not you could have more cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what about to drink, as a child, what did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I had tea pretty early I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And would you have had anything other than things like bread and butter and cake, meat, or cheese?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. Oh we sometimes had shrimps. Strawberries in season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What did your parents eat in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, fish and they might have boiled bacon, I think they were easily prepared meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A lighter meal than lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, just that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just one course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 One course, then probably cheese. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And any more tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, that was water then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How often a day do you think they would have had tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well they would have it for tea, and probably that's all, then they might have a cup of Olvatine, that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not generally tea, they weren't great tea drinkers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No coffee at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Very seldom. Oh yes, very seldom, and they had that awful Camp coffee. With a lot of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But not a regular daily thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. I think we could have it in the morning if we wanted to, but that was almost, you would have the thing on
 the table and you could make it with hot water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What sort of tea was it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well this was, you see my father sold it, it would have been a blend of Indian teas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What do you know about how food supplies were got. I mean your f
ather was a grocer wasn't he. Did all the good come from the shop, in the way of provisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Everything you could get you see. And of course we grew our own vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You didn't buy vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just fruit from this man you mentioned?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Just occasional foreign fruit. In season we would have all our own apples, we grew our own asparagus. We had quite a big garden, there were tomatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about bread? Do you know how bread was got for the household.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well it was delivered you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That, yes, I don't know how that was chosen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did somebody come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no, no. My mother would have gone down to the butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 On her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and possibly it was delivered. But she would have selected it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That would have been the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She would have gone to the shop herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you know if she went to any other food shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, doesn't that embrace? She would hav
e her own butcher and fishmonger you see, and as I say all the groceries - it seems like more or less everything, yes, I just wondered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't think that would leave anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just meat and fish she would look after, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But she would order the other things you see. It wouldn't be my rather who would order them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I wonder if we have covered all their entertainments? Pubs, well that's out. The seaside you told me about. Oh yes, did you dress differently on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. Best suits on Sundays all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Right from the moment you got up, different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. I mean it was the most dismal day of the week for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have to, I mean you couldn't do any sort of rough games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. This went on the whole time I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about newspapers and periodicals read at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well we had the daily paper of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What was it, local or national?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 National. "Daily News" I think it was. And of course the local weekly paper. No Sunday paper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Any weeklies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I had my own "Boys Own" paper. Or was it Arthur Mee's(?) - no "Childrens magazine".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 "Children's Newspaper"?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There was "Childrens Newspaper" and "My Magazine" I think they called it. By Arthur Mee. I had bot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9852899\charrsid1014503 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  of those. I don't think they had anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did they let you read the grown up papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, as soon as I could read. There was nothing I liked better than a good murder trial!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They didn't mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I don't know whether they knew. I mean, what I was reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You didn't feel any sort of censorship on their part? Partial censorship anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think there was a - you see as soon as I could I got books from the library. I read quite a lot in those days. I don't think they had the
 knowledge of censorship, I don't think they knew what I was reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You mean in the paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, in the books I got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think you got books that they wouldn't have approved of?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I am sure I did. I can't remember them all now - I mean they didn't read novels you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did they not read novels at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. Well I mean yes. When they were younger, Charles Kingsley and Dickens you see. They were all right from their point of view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Why did you say when they were younger? Had they given up reading by the time you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I don't think they were, my father was generally reading travel books - he was quite keen on travel you see. He took me to the whole family to in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Switzerland
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} when I was fourteen. They were quite early days to take a family over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would that have been just after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just after - the 14/18 War, must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he read books about explorations? Archeology, that sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well archeology wasn't really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Some excavations had been done hadn't they the excavations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes, a certain amount had. But it was largely a matter of the finds they had got. It was really in its infancy in those days. I dare say he would be. But there wouldn't have been many books on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember any of the travel books?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you remember Kingsley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Charles Kingsley and Dickens were favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I am just remembering at the moment -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Walter Scott?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Walter Scott of course. Say they did read Walter Scott? Or had read them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think perhaps your father didn't have a great deal of time for reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, he didn't. He wouldn't at that period I suppose. No, it wasn't that he wouldn't read, I think p
ossibly that might have been the explanation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How many evenings a week, for example, would he spend on work to do with his mission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well he would have all Sunday you see. And then there was Wednesday evening meetings, occasionally they would hav
e these open air services like the Salvation Army you see. I was pulled in from time to time, much to my embarrassment yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you ever have any enthusiasm for the religious side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I think I had a - at that time I think it was largely embarra
ssment. I had a feeling towards the morality side of the whole, of religion, you see. But I was always rather critical.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Of the services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh definitely of the services then. And of course I was very frightened too, you see I believed in the seco
nd coming of Christ. And they always felt it was quite imminent you see. Well, and it created a real fear in my early - because I knew I wasn't good enough to go up you see. And I always thought that my mother and father, they would go, they were so good 
you see - and it was a real fear. Yes, yes. I don't think I ever told this to my parents, I have never told it to anybody, but it was always within me. If they were late, you know, coming back from anywhere "Where have they gone?"
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How interesting. Was it something that was dwelt on a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, at that period of their lives. When it didn't happen -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They did actually fix a day did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They didn't, no. They just felt what with wars and rumou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4460424\charrsid1014503 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 s of wars, you know, the prophesy o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4460424\charrsid1014503 f the Bible was coming to fulfi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
lment and that Christ would come down, up they would go, well that's how I thought of it. I don't quite know if they really felt it that way, I think they did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about hell? Was that dwelt on much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no. It was, no 
there wasn't anything of that. It was this or the love of God, it was to encourage one, one might say, on the good side. No there was no frightening on hell.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 The only fear then that you think you got from this religion was the fear that you might be separated from them on the second coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well at that period that was a fear yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 At about what age would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, I should say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 In your teens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No earlier than that. I would have been tenish. You see when I got to
 my teens, I was just going to say I was awfully rude to my mother you see. And this always created a feeling in the - I mean it is a natural growing up period of my early feens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You hadn't been up to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No more than any I suppose normal boy,
 you see, I was full of spirits and everything. But I knew it got them down, very much. I was very very critical of my mother, she didn't dress well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That would worry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I would laugh at her. You know. Don't put that silly old hat on!" And 
the result was "Well Norris, you will have to go to boarding school" and I think I told you I nearly went to Leighton Park (?) and would have gone, only I was thirteen at that time and I was too old to go. I was very keen to go. I think it would have done
 me good, personally. My parents were too much on top of me, I mean I wanted a bit of independence, I didn't get that until I was seventeen or eighteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think your parents really hadn't wanted you to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 My mother didn't. I remember the first time I left home she cried and cried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I was seventeen or eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Why do you think you became conscious of the way she dressed? Do you remember people passing remarks about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I think I probably just liked to see a woman dress well. It certainly wasn't anything more then that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did she disapprove of dressing well or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She disapproved of being in the fashion. I mean, what she wore was good, but it certainly wasn't tasteful, and it was
 old fashioned you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But neat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, yes. My father was the opposite, he was always spic and span. Well got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes. What about, I want to talk to you a bit more about meals. Were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well a certain amount when the family was there but if we visitors, as we often had, (end of tape)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Now, at school, you were telling me a story actually, why don't you carry on with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well that was one of the greatest disappointments and anger, one of the first ti
mes I was really angry. The whole of the class had arranged to go to a Shakespeare play in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and I had said I would go, this was when I was about 14 or 15, and my parents wouldn't let me go. And it was the first time I had felt how unreasonable they w
ere. They had nothing against Shakespeare as such, it was going to a theatre. And I suppose it was the first time in my life, I did have a real feeling that they were wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not just that it was inconvenient for you, but they were actually misguided in this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, that is the thing which made me angry and disappointed. This went on within me for weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, did you have arguments about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were allowed to argue with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But they didn't convince you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And I couldn't convince them either.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was this the first big difference you can remember on a question of principle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, I was a - yes, up to that time I would accept their ruling as right, I even if I wanted somethin
g. But, no it was the injustice I felt strongly at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes. What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh it was just, they call it a county school, it was equivalent, I suppose, to a Grammar School then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I suppose we should go actually back to your first school. That was the first school of any kind you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well that was a preparatory, co-educational school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was that a council school or a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It was private, run by two spinsters, and I went when I
 was five. I remember doing, what do you call it, pothooks, in a copy book on my first day there. I think that I enjoyed my time there, I mean I have got no memories of not being happy there. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember what sort of a building it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It was like a big house, well it was a large house and they lived there as well, yes, probably bought specially to turn it into a school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were there desks or tables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Desks to start with. There was an enormous big, well to my childish memo
ry, a large room, very large room, and I remember they had bars for gymnastics up on one wall there, and they had several classes running in the same room. Well they had girls up to, I don't know what age, older anyway, and one of the teachers just dealt 
with the older ones, probably had an assistant, I can't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Boys and girls were kept together in the little ones, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we were together, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And the girls stayed on and the boys left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 The boys left at what, well I left at eight, whether they went on to eleven I don't know. No, I think boys left at about eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and did you all face the same way with the desks all in rows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9245206\charrsid1014503 No, no. It was higg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9245206\charrsid1014503 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 dy-piggeldy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were they, thinking of modern schools, do you think it was fairly modern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think that it was quite a modern school for that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were mentioning the gymnastic bars -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and then they had the ropes there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you do any painting, or any of those sort of craft things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes we did. We had to draw I remember. From memory, you know, crayon I think, I don't think that we did ordinary painting there. Crayon I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 In the drawing were you given a subject or could you draw freely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We could draw freely, although we were told sometimes to bring a flower or leaf, and then we would draw that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have nature walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And music, any musical activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, what about percussion band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And reading, how did they teach the reading, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Could you read when you went to school actually? Had you learnt at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 At five. I could tell the time I know. I sort of, to a certain extent, taught myself to read from cartoon thing, Tiger Tim and whatnot.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, did you have those at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes, these came in my magazine, at least one page of them. No, we didn't have comic cuts, the magazine, but there were the, couple of pages in these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you taught yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I know that that was the first reading I did. I can't remember them actually teaching us reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When you went to school did you have uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, except at, I think we might have had a cap. No, we didn't have a definite uniform, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were the other children mostly from middle class backgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember any children who you felt were very different in their background from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They wouldn't have been there I don't think. But I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember any children who were in any way teased or felt out of things -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I think it was quite a happy atmosphere there. My sister assisted later there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did she? Did you have lunches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But I would only go there in the morning I think to start with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we were quite close.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What were your parents attitude's to your first school? Do you remember at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember them asking you what you did or talking much about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No. But I would come home full of talk, like Stephen does, you know, and things which impressed me during the day at school, and of course that would occupy the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And they were interested in talking to you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Up to a point. I mean I wasn't pushed off in any way at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
You didn't get that feeling that I remember very much from childhood that your parents were pre-occupied with things that didn't concern one so one couldn't get through to them with ones own interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, they were very good in their way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes, they talked to you. Can you remember any special occasions at school, things like an open day or Carol Service, or prize giving, or anything of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What in that preparatory school? No, I can't 
remember. I can only remember there was, going down, they had a sort of dingy cloakroom in the cellar there. I can remember this place, but I can't remember any incidents.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And about the teachers, do you remember their attitudes to children at all? How they dealt with them, punished them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Let's take you on to the next school, the council -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 County - well they called it the working {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}County
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} you see. It was partly scholarship - grants - county grants for boys you see, from the County.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So they would have been first, eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, and I went in the preparatory part at eight you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That would have been all fee paying, I imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That would have been all fee paying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was it boys or co-ed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no, all boys. Yes, and then after the two years, you go into a class where about a third were scholarship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember the scholarship boys as being in any way different to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I think there was a, there was a definite fee
ling, I think it was largely a question that they were cleverer than most of us! And they sat together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was that their own choice or were they sat together by the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I wonder, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But they did sit together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They did t
o start with, I know. That might have, you know, you would forget they were scholarship boys afterwards. But I think the cleavage between the two, we all felt that they had more brains, and there was quite a competition to see whether we could beat them y
ou see it wasn't a class feeling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, you don't remember any differences in clothes or the way they spoke or behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about the teachers attitude to them? Do you remember the teachers behaving in any way differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't think there was any difference there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Except they might with the cleverest ones be more encouraged I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember if they held their own at being near the top, most of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Certain ones did, but I think quite a number didn't, you know I am certain of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about groupings in the school, gangs and cliques, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, well I suppose two years of my life which were the most miserable was when I was in the prep. You see there were two cl
asses in the Prep and once came out half an hour before the other and there must have been a bully in the top class of the Prep and they absolutely bullied these younger ones, and I mean I suffered a real fear over that period and I daren't say anything t
o my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Because they frightened you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I mean if it got back to them that I had said something to my parents and the master came in and said you know, I would get it worse. That was the attitude. I mean I have told you all about this. Duck yo
u in the lavatory basin and S.C. Yes. They would man the gates you see, we had to go through a playground you see, and then out through iron gates, they would shut that and I suppose there were about a dozen, I mean I remember being shut in a dustbin and 
then they make you say things, make you promise to do this it was all right, and then they would finish up filling your cap with water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And this went on for two years you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well a good year at any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think the teachers found out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I think something did leak out in the end, because it stopped. I can't remember if it was because of a change of class, you know, it might have been that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think your mother realized that something was worrying you? Did she ever ask you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, but you know one is a bit resilient at that age I think. Whilst one fears this, when you are out of it you do tend to forget it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 On your whole, were your relationships with the children good, at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. I go
t, later on you see I think that first stage well you didn't know the other boys. It takes quite a time to create a friendship I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you didn't feel shy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember worries of getting on with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I asked this partly because you said you didn't have children at home much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But at school you had quite an easy relationship with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember a typical school day? How the day started?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well I can remember how the day started, with morning prayers, we all had to file in and, in classes, in the main hall there and the headmaster said prayers and then we sang some sort of chant for about five minutes. Then we had twenty minutes scripture, 
every morning you see, in classes, and well then the various subjects came up, they would be about forty minutes each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And the break for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 We had a five minutes break in the morning you see. In the playground. And then a break, I think, fro
m twelve to two. And then we went on to half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 This was from eight to ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, this was after ten. We came out a good half an hour earlier at the Prep you see. Otherwise I think it was the same, we came out at four instead of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past four{\*\xmlclose} you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were you keen on schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I had the subjects I liked, and some I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What did you like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I was always very very keen on Geography. I found that I could always be top of the class in that one thing. Looking back 
now, I think that it was probably quite a good teacher. And I did enjoy the subject. I was no good at English. And Mathematics I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about languages, did you do any other languages?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I just did German you see. In the Prep they tried us off with French, but I didn't get anywhere with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just German, no Latin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No Latin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Could you have done Latin if you had wanted to? At none of the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about things like Art and Music? Did you enjoy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, not particularly. Music, it was just singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I remember you said you didn't care for playing the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh there was no piano taught in school, that was done with a private teacher. I don't think, I think that Art was extra. I didn't take Art.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Drawing, that sort of thing? But in school generally, do you feel that your parents encouraged you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but not on higher education. I would have liked to have gone to university, you see, and they, I mean the attitude was, well yo
u can do what you like, but I didn't know how to do it, and there was no master at school really to advise. I feel I wasted my opportunity in that period, now, looking back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They had no ambition for you scholastically?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I mean if I had expre
ssed a desire for any different job or profession, I wouldn't have met with opposition. But there was this business waiting for me you see, and I wasn't really adverse to it. I felt I wanted to go to university, but there wasn't a real good sixth from the
re on their own after the matriculation level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Where do you think you got the idea of going to university?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well you see I wasn't that keen on going into the business, not that I was really adverse to it, but I felt I wanted - but I didn't quite k
now what.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I am wondering how you got the idea of university at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I knew there were, well my friend John }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2452872\charrsid1014503 Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 ell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2452872\charrsid1014503 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
, I was with him at school, but he went on to Goldsmiths you see, the teachers college. I didn't, I wanted further education, w
hen - said university I meant further education. But then the whole question in my mind at that time, that's useless unless you know what you are going to do, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you were just not given the help to try and get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I wanted to do more on my Geography, for example, I seemed to memorise everything in that way, and enjoyed it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would you have liked to stay on longer at school than you did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I would have, but - I did stay on a bit longer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How old were you when you left actually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh seventeen I think. I did stay on, but I soon realized after a couple of terms that it was not leading anywhere you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about social functions at school, did you go to them, did they have plays and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
You see this period was largely during the war period, the 14/18 War and this was a great disadvantage. I mean, a lot of the staff went, and a lot of things were discontinued, it was a bad time to be at school. We did have a Sports Day. It did
n't mean much to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't have memories of your parents with the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, there was no contact between my parents and the teaching staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They didn't come to your home, or your parents come to school to see them, that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Your educational progress wasn't discussed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think that it was general in the school, you don't remember comparing your parents with other parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, it was just sort of accepted. I don't think that there was any contact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No open days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. I assume that if parents had problems they would have contacted the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but there wasn't a parent-teacher association, anything of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about school reports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh they were pleased if I was near the top you see. And I was very pleased too, if I could get it. But they didn't worry me, didn't worry the parents to that extent. I mean if I was doing badly I wouldn't a row from them you see. I mean Marion (?) w
ould have been different there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They were ambitious for her education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, if things went wrong, you know, it would accept the child I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you sum up what your parents general attitude to the school was? How do you think they saw th
e school, if they thought about it much. What was the job they thought the school ought to be doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I think that they would just look at it upon, almost reading, writing and arithmetic and gaining a certain amount of knowledge. I think that that really would probably sum up their attitude.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They didn't expect the school to do anything like teaching you how to behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There was this queer position that I was telling you about, threatened to go to a boarding school, when they felt that there
 I should be taught how to behave. So they didn't anticipate that a day school would give that tuition. I think that was probably their -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Religious training - did they in any way wonder what the school taught you? Query that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, they didn't query that at all, they didn't query that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about a uniform there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just a cap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just a cap again. In other words you wore what you liked, that was the same through all the schools you went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I am not actually quite clear yet on the division between the Prep and the Senior. Was it in one building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 In the one building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There was no formal division then between the two?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but as you said at the beginning it was all fee paying. When I say fees it
 was a very small amount, I think it was about four pounds a term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Can you remember if there was anything interesting about the schools? Curriculum you see, one can find this out, this is all sort of in books, you know what people were actually taught
 and how they were taught it, but incidents, particularly really on the relationships say with the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well the matter of discipline was quite different. This varied from teacher to teacher. I mean there was this tendency with some of them to s
trike you or hit you with a ruler you see. And they, if you were sent to the headmaster you see, you got the stick. The cane, you know, this thin thing, there on the hand, you see. Well that was a fearful thing until you got it. I suppose for the first th
ree years I didn't have it. Once I had had it, it was like going to the confessional, all cleaned off then!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have it often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not so many as some, about half a dozen times in all the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would you rate yourself as good, bad or average on behaviour generally at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I suppose I was average. And then there was rather a lot of, there was a certain amount of bullying going on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about prefects, sort of authority among the boys themselves? Did you have promotion in any kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we had - no we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No prefects at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about duties among the boys? School monitors, nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How interesting. Did the staff then do, all the things that in some school
s the prefects do, like, well seeing that the classrooms were kept tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh it never was tidy. I mean it was cleaned out by cleaners in the evening you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Looking after lost property, seeing that children file in and out of class and the playground quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That would have been done by the master you see. Or mistress, there were women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what about things like the teachers punishments. Can you remember anything else besides this whack with a ruler or going to the Head?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh there were lines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Learning by heart?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Once or twice the head would give this, instead of the stick, if it was a whole group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember anything you did learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can remember trying to learn something, and that was, you see I've always found it very very difficult to memorise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Poetry, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You say that you found Geography quite easy to remember though. You were interested I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I think that's what it is, I can remember places, and 
dates, and things like that. But when it comes to "Learn this" and there were about a dozen of us that had been mucking about and he luckily just picked on two to recite it and missed me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember that it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3803130\charrsid1014503 What's the name "Raz}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 erra's Ride" is that a well known piece?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Is it by Flecker or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember, No, No. I think Marian knows, I will ask her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Any other kind of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about school attendance? Did you have any problems in that way, did you ever play truant, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no. I was occasionally ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A note?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A note, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about rewards, prizes? What was the incentive to work well, I gather that the school of wasn't ambitious in that it
 didn't send a lot of people to university. Would the staff drive you very hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, I think it was pretty poor looking --------- I think we did have a - did we have a prize giving? I don't know. You know it just hasn't registered very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember prizes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And marks, points, you know, that sort of thing, did you have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Marks, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Gold stars, did you have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, we just had the marks. And form places you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you sit in places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have house teams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, we had three houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And did they compete against each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Only in sports.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was team spirit, or house spirit, something the staff used a lot to get you keen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not anything like a Public school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think that just about covers school now, can you think of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think that the fact that these things didn't make much of any impression on you shows that the weren't driven ver
y hard by the staff. You know. I am very interested that you said that there wasn't any kind of prefect or monitors or captains of class, there must have been captains in sport, surely, you have team captains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You see we had this, as I said during th
e war period, and the sports ground was a long way away from school and we were having a certain amount of these Zepelin raids and that went largely by the board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. It has got here, for meals, did you help yourselves? You said that, 
you told me about breakfast, at lunch you were waited on, everything would have been handed to you, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
The plates were brought round, yes. I think Mother had the vegetables up her end of the table and Father had the meat he carved the meat you
 see, and the maid would take the plate from my Father, after he had cut the meat, take it round to my Mother who would serve the vegetables and then take it round to whoever it is, in turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I see, and the pudding, what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember, that, I rather think that she wouldn't be there, I think that would be the end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And with the tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh she wouldn't be in then at all, except taking the tea in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember what you called her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh we called her by her Christian name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You say you called her by her first name - the cook as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And the gardener?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh, by the surname - er - Peoples.(?)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what did they call you, personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think they called me Master Norris.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Madam and Sir, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
How were you, can you remember being told how to behave towards them, or being given any idea of what they were like, how they felt about things, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I do remember, as I said
 earlier on, there was a tendency of me ragging this, she was an old cook you see, and I would go in there and mess the kitchen about, something like that, I mean I was told off very much, I mean I had to behave myself as far as she was concerned you see.
 The gardener, we looked upon him as a craftsman you see, and I worked quite a lot with him. Learnt gardening from him you see. And I mean one looked up to him and you had to be very careful how you dealt with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, your parents didn't need to tell you there to watch out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
And with the various younger girls that you had, what would your mother have called them do you think? Sorry, were they housemaids, parlour maids or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I don't know that she - I suppose - I don't know what she
 called them. She wouldn't use a word for it, you know we just want somebody to help us - I don't know. I mean {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was called a cook, I mean - yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And did anyone else come in, you said somebody came in, you thought, to take you for walks? Did anyo
ne else. What about laundry, how was the laundry and washing done in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Er - I think a certain amount of the laundry went out to the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember a washing woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no. We didn't have anybody. I think, you know, anything heavy went to the laundry, was collected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And what about mending and sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well my Mother would do most of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember any other people who came in to do regular jobs in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I mean these, like Mrs. Manning here, we would have somebody like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But she didn't come into the house, your mother would go to her would she? Do you remember people coming in and sewing in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your Mother have 
people to stay - you did mention visitors. At one time you said your Mother didn't entertain much, were these people staying in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well we had a lot come for this {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Mission{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} you see. Missionaries would come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 From abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 From abroad. And then any hard luck cases we would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 have in sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 From the neighbourhood do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, not from the neighbourhood. It was all the different contacts from other Churches. For instance, well we had a whole group of missionaries arrived 
at Tilbury with smallpox, well they were put in the isolation house, well my Father had them all at our place. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Really, though they were contacts for smallpox?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well they had gone through the isolation hospital and were waiting, I think i
t was a family of six missionaries and I vividly remember they kept one of them in the hospital and the mother, no it was the sister, wailing at night, when I was quite a small boy, and they lost two or three of them. I mean that was the sort of thing my 
people would do. During the war we had a Refugee baby for two years you see. Yes. A Belgian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A year, when he or she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 He.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 With nobody - just the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Just the baby, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How did your mother get him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think that was a suggestion from Auntie Carrie(?) Who was a nurse at the time and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Had the baby been orphaned in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Belgium{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It wasn't orphaned, they were separated, something to do with the Germans, with the advance, I can't remember the wh
ole situation but I know that we had this child for two months because he got like a brother to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Two months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 For Twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 A year to two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I am not quite certain, but it was long enough to become one of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember how that baby was looked after at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember who looked after it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your mother spend much time with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She would, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember anything, it is not something that would interest you, that aspect of the baby I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't remember at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't remember that sort of thing about my sister, for example. But you yourself were keen on the baby, played with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. I remember crying when it left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And your Father, do you remember his attitude to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh he was taken on anything like that, and would welcome it. He had a wonderful sympathetic side to him, and he it would be nothing for him, if he heard that somebody was sick, to spend the night with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Wonderful. Did he play with it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 The child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I can't remember that. I mean it is a bit young for playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I just wondered, you don't remember him taking it out in the pram or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about health, that's the one thing we haven't touched on really. Health, doctors and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I told you, we never had a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 On principle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was that on religious principle do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They didn't believe in doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well they, they, I think that they were a bit muddled with it because I think it depended how ill you were. I mean they weren't like Christian Scientists you see, on the other hand they believed that if you prayed you
 could have faith in getting better. On the other hand -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about dentists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, we went to the dentist. And gave me a fear of dentists for the rest of my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But doctors and illness, didn't play a part in your life? Your mother's asthma you mentioned, what sort of remedies would she take for that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh she had a special smoke thing - um - I mean looking back now the treatment I had when I had a temperature and things, was the right one, I don't think that anybody could do better,
 as long as there weren't complications. And I think that they would have called in a doctor if there had been. But they didn't run to a doctor unless it was vitally necessary.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. Do you remember your parents attitude to how much food you ate, a
nd did you have to eat everything on the table or finish the portion you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That is a part of table manners isn't it, how much you eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. You were expected to eat up what was on our plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were you allowed to eat everything that was served up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well sometimes for example, I just wondered, some things like curry, would you have been allowed to eat things like curry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think so. I think we all had the same. I mean I remember the dislike of some
 things, and they would say "Have a bit" you know. Peas, for example, I just couldn't eat them, peas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Usually a favourite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but it wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They wouldn't make you? Just a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. To save an enormous row, I think they kept it down to a very small amount.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, but it would be definitely trying it every time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That's what it seemed like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And sweets. Did they play any part in your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I had a very small pocket money, sixpence, or was it threepence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It went up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It didn't go up very much. I used to buy penny worths on the way to school you see, there was no, I mean I could have what I wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And um, any kind of ways of earning extra money. Did you ever get any money -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, there wasn't any, I don't think I was given money much at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It didn't figure in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What about presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Presents, there was rather a tendency to put it in our savings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Money you were given as presents, were you given other presents, toys and that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, Christmas and Birthdays, yes. They were quite lavish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You know, by bicycles and tricycles and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 There wasn't a feeling of poverty, I mean I know your parents were poor, but the feeling that poverty was a good religious thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh no. I mean my Father enjoyed life, there is no doubt about that. And looking back I must feel that he must have found religion an awful handicap!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When did he get religious? Or was he always religious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, he told me that he got, when he, he had a very serious illness when he was about fifteen or sixteen, he never went bac}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3803130\charrsid1014503 k to school, he had his appendix}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  out in one of the first operations for it, and I thin
k this sort of preyed upon him, because he thought he was going to die, and he told me that they used to have these big parties and he went and he had a cousin there who was pretty filthy mouthed you see. And that seemed to get him on edge, and then I don
't know, some change came in. He would have been attending, at that time, Congregational Church you see. And then he and Mr. Williamson, bought the business in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Gravesend{\*\xmlclose}
, with a wine and spirit licence you see. Well my father was never particularly keen on seeing this beer go out, particularly round Christmas, the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3803130\charrsid1014503 re was an enormous lot of drunken}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 ness in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Gravesend{\*\xmlclose}
, I mean it is a dock town and I mean, I can quite understand his attitude to drink at that time. And he thought he was responsible for it and there
 came a stage at that time when they were going to part company you see and my Father was going down to Working and Mr. Williamson was going to carry on in Gravesend. And then he gave, he was rather keen on this good work that was being done by this Missi
o
n you see, and he gave them quite a large contribution, and the woman Superintendent refused the money, because it had been earned on drink. And this so much sort of hit him that he, after that he felt the same as my father, and they gave up the licence y
ou see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I see, was it quite a drop for them financially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well it was a very profitable part of the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They really felt it themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well, I mean, they had this moral feeling which one admires.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, of course. And that, can you remember that, or was it before your memory, were you told about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I can remember all this. Well when I say, I mean it was all, it happened before my memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But it was recent enough for them to tell, you, can you remember a date when that might have happened, about 1900 or earlier?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well this would probably have happened about 1908, something like that. Yes. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When was your father born actually? Do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh dear me, you see he died when he was about 72 or 4 what would he be, in his thirties I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't know when he died, what year did he die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I just wondered how old was he when you were born, do you know that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. Of course he was always on the minority side,
 you know. Wouldn't worry about public opinion didn't affect him at all, what people thought about him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, and your Mother in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, she wouldn't worry. She was much, my Father was more tolerant than my Mother, was just like this you see
. But if Father felt a thing he would say it you see. Which I always found from the child's point of view was very embarrassing. You see if he would go into a Non-Smoking Railway carriage and see somebody am king, he would tell them about it you see. On t
h
e other hand he wouldn't mind old men smoking, he always used to say "Well they are enjoying that" he wouldn't mind that. But little things like that, which as a child you know, I found terribly embarrassing. If he felt that I should do this, he jolly wel
l would. If he went into a Church and heard the parson say something with which he didn't agree, he would wait until he had, end of the Service and go up and see him and tell him what he thought about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What would you say your father's political views were, that you remember when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I - I can - I can't remember him discussing politics as such - at all, at least {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lot
{\*\xmlclose} party politics. I mean, he was very interested on the social life of people and particularly the poor people. B
ut - I - I - I don't know which party he voted for at all, I couldn't say now. He always said that - ballot was secret and he wouldn't telly anybody which side he voted on and as a business man he felt that it was - wasn't good policy to - to - declare wh
ere he - which side he favoured. Although I should imagine he would be on the Liberal side if - but I can only guess that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You guess that from his general attitudes to society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes. But I - in his own business he - the - shop was opposite the - Town Hall where the poll was declared and on - that }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 might}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
 he - for a number of years would allow the Conservatives to use one room and the Liberals to use another room, one being above the other. This carried on for a good many years until fireworks we
re exchanged from window to the other and - after that he wouldn't let - allow either party to use the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was any damage actually done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't think really but - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It put him off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember him getting in any par
ticular issues of the time, what was his attitude for example to the first world war when that broke out, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh he - he was a conscientious objector and - from religious grounds, not political grounds. And he took a leading part in defe
nding - young people and - oh - he what would he be in his forties then and then he was - called up eventually towards the end of the war and - but he was classified - on health grounds and he wasn't called up but he - he wouldn't have - joined - because 
of his religious being that it was wrong to kill anybody, that was his attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When you say he was defending young people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I'm sorry, I'm thinking that in the second word war. No, in the first world war he would have been the - the one. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you know if your mother had any views of her own on politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't think so at all, she never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 discussed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  it and I think she'd just follow what he - in fact I very much doubt whether she voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You mean you think in 1918 when women got the vote she didn't cast her vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't - I - I should very much doubt it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember her ever commenting or saying anything about the suffragettes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, no, it wouldn't - I don't think mother - that would have - interested at all, I think she would have been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She wouldn't have had any opinions about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember what her attitude was to things like the rights of the working man and his position and this kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, she wasn't articulate on that - on that side at all. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But he did talk about that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not - not quite in that - in that - in that way. I mean - I think one would rather look upon him - he was a very good - employer and -
 but he was particularly a religious man and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
 interests were rather on that side, possibly on charitable grounds more than - that political.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you know if anybody ever approached him and asked him to take a part in party politics or canvassed hi
m or suggested he stood for any council or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I know he was - asked to be a Justice of Peace and he turned it down. Largely again he said, there might come a time when I would have to commit a man - he might be a - face the position 
where I'd meet a murderer and I'd feel that I was responsible for his hanging and - this would again go right against the grain for him. And I - I remember him telling me that was - the reason why he - he turned it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What was his attitude then to capital punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well he felt that no - man had the right to - take life. Just that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So he was against capital punishment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh absolutely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It's very consistent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not all religious people are consistent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, well he was on that as well as fighting, I mean, all for - the whole thing's wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
At that time do you remember any cases of people voting a certain way because their employers felt that they ought to - putting pressure on them, did you ever hear people talking about this, before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I don't - in - among - at that time. Only I've heard it more recently really, you might say, in the country districts. Not there, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When your father gave these rooms and these fireworks were going off were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No, I was too young I think. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember any political activity on the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I used to go to - public meetings around and - remember the enormous crowds which - which came there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember any particular speaker you went to hear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. I - I - I don't. No, I can't remember the names and I don't think it was anybody of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you go to both parties or just one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You know, I just really can't remember, I - I - I th
ink I went to the Liberal man, I can't even remember his name now. But - I don't think I - as a boy gave great deal, I think it was more for the excitement I think and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you heckle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I didn't heckle, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Because there was a lot then wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you ever remember going round in a band shouting slogans or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No, no, I don't think there was a great deal of that in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Gravesend{\*\xmlclose}
. I mean people wear their ribbon you see but not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Pubs, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was he a member of any sort of club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not any - no, he spent nearly all his time on - on religious work. One or two societies he was interested in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What were those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Rose Society in which he was judge for quite a large district round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he grow a lot of roses himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, he was very keen gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You said that grace was always said }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 at meals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Who was it who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 My father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 None of the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You said you kept hens as a child, did you keep anything else like pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh rabbits, during the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 To eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How did you feel about them being killed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I used to - me personally you mean? Oh I used to work round and try and see the ga}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid552511\charrsid1014503 rdener kill them. Yes that was c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 uriosity I think at that time. Geese and ducks and chickens. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And you had that job of cleaning out the hen house didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, yes, I told you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Until what age did you have to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I don't know - ten - twelve I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you carry on after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 At meal times were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Up to a point but I - I think if I remember rightly if we had visitors we - we were expected to keep silent unless we were spoken to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh frequently, yes. Again, largely for - people who came to the - for this mission you see, who - speakers. Practicall
y every weekend we - we had them and - oh yes, we had quite a lot of people to - during the week and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What meals would they come to if they came to a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Ah we used to - they used to - stay there you see. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Didn't you have some missionaries who'd been in contact with small pox or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Oh yes, we had them in the house for a week or so, yes. And then again - we have - we had sort of more or less refugees in you see and - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So you had people both coming for odd meals and people staying in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Yes. You see, my father and mother were very sort of - sympathetic and tender hearted and first war we had a - a Belgian baby for two years you see, I don't know whether I told you that, yes, well thi
s is sort of thing - suddenly sort of decide to do this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But generally when there weren't guests there what was the attitude towards conversation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I can't remember what was discussed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were you allowed to have long talks, stop eating for a long period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, I - I think we had a - a fair say and - but we had to get on with our meal and and - you know, there wasn't unlimited time but - our parents were very interested in what we had done at - sister and I - at school and - they'd listen and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They used to ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, and - and - yes, there was quite a - free conversation on that line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, you said you didn't like peas, were you made to eat some peas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. But generally not many you know sort of it was - sort of a discipline to do - to sort of - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You weren't allowed to pick and choose and say what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. For tea you see you were supposed to have bread and butter or something before you got to the cake and - and they stuck to that, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were you allowed to bring a toy or a book to the table ever as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember when you could leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh it was sort of - the end - please may I get down? You had to say this you see, then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you have to wait until everybody was finished or could you get down when you'd finished what they considered a proper meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think we generally had a feed but then of course - we - I - I 
don't think I had my meals always with the parents you see during the week. Definitely when I was at school I think I - I used - lunch at any rate I would have - very often on my own too. And then I know I used to say things I would like and they used to 
cook these, I mean previously they knew what I liked and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Where would your mother be then when you were having lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh I don't know, just wandering about I expect, but she wouldn't be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Would she have hers at another time then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I think she must have had it with - yes, I think I - had to come home a bit earlier than my father did at that time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And she'd wait and eat with him would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your sister have lunch with you do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Not on those occasions, I don't know where she was, she must have had it with - with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 But you always came home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I did. Yes, I didn't have lunch at school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember your mother actually putting you to bed at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Tucking you in and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. Every night. And bathing every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember what age you were when she stopped doing that and you took yourself off to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I can't - I can't say on that - I kn
ow she wanted to bath me long after I felt I was capable of doing it myself. I can remember I was annoyed about this you now. She was persistent seeing I was clean I think. But - it's very difficult to remember ages. Must have been, you know, thirteen or 
something like that - twelve or thirteen I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 She was still tucking you in and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I don't know about tucking me in, no. Well - I think if I remember rightly when would sort of I would go to bed possibly and read you see 
and she'd come up and - and see that the lights were out at a certain time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were supposed to come and say goodnight to both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. See my father'd be working until - see he wouldn't come in 'til nine or - eight, nine or ten at night yo
u see. He'd come home for tea. We'd see him then. But - oh then he'd go back to business you see. So that - we would be in bed before he came back. Yes. During the week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Very long hours weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did he have some supper or something before he went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes, always had a - a supper. Eight or nine you see. Yes, yes. yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 When you were a schoolboy do you remember if they were particular about the time that you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I - it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was there quite a routine about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Within half an hour or so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember what it was roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I suppose about - when I was about twelve I should think it'd be about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 That's quite early isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Even in summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh eight to nine I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember thinking it was about the same as other boys or did it seem earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well I didn't have any - sort of - contact with the - see we were - we were living in a - poor neighbourho
od. And I - and we - I mean, I didn't play with those boys at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you ever try to when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well when I was younger I had - there was sort of jealousy I think with me and - and the contacts I had more fights than play. I mean -
 they were - they - I - I - I had contacts, yes, I did with - another boy opposite who went to the same school as I did you see, yes, we - we played together, but I can't remember any conflict about going to bed at night. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So that wasn't something you felt your mother was trying to baby you about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Those children, when you had these fights with them, do you remember how you felt about it at the time, whether you told your parents and what they said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I was - I was frightened,
 there's no doubt about that and - I suppose - I don't know whether I did tell them or - they didn't do anything about it. I - I - I think I'd keep this to myself. And I think I told you earlier about bullying at school, I mean - yes - I - I - I mean I - 
no, I kept these things to myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you ever remember them telling you that you shouldn't play with certain children? Putting any taboos on certain playmates for any reason?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can't remember instances on - on that. Wasn't - definitely wasn't encouraged but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Do you think they concerned themselves at all about the fact that you didn't play with local children, that you didn't have much social life, you rather resented this didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think they perhaps didn't think it mattered then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, I think - I wonder what their attitude was - I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You don't remember them saying anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, they wouldn't say - give any reason really. No. I mean, looking back I suppose - there was a - possibly more
 discipline from my people in a friendly way whilst - I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I think people possibly are much more anxious about their children having playmates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Well I know it was a wrong thing to do and - to - to - not to encourage more -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You feel it was bad for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I do, looking back, yes. But - I don't think I - I realised at that time. I mean I - I - I - I think I had this close friend - who - who lived opposite and then of course I got very friendly with John Flellow you reme
mber, that was in - when I was fifteen or sixteen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So you weren't friendless?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh no. No. Oh no. And I had - oh no, I had plenty of - schoolfriends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It was just you didn't have children coming into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Into the house, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did you always have your own room or did you share a room with Pauline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, always had my own room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 How many bedrooms would there have been in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh - well there - there was - four on - plus the attic bedrooms where they - servants, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 So your parents had one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 And Pauline had one and you had one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I had one then there's a spare room and I think there was another small single room, yes, there was another single room as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you remember your mother mending the clothes at all, do you remember her sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes. Yes. And - she had other people sewing as well. She also did sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You mean the servants did some sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No, they - no, they - no they didn't but she'd - sometimes have a woman in or take - clothes - to - to - to be done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were those to be mended or were they new clothes that she had done by that woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh perhaps they were new, I don't know, but mother did - mother did a lot of sewing and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember what they thought about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, you just didn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was there ever an incident where they caught you swearing or didn't you swear as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I - oh I think I - yes, I think in the latter bit I did and
 you know was told off about it. Well I mean nothing much more than damn or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did they consider it a particularly bad things, swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh yes, they - they thought it was very bad. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Were you allowed to join in when they were talking either to each other about things or their own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
I - I think we were up to a point but I mean - if it was a - a confidential conversation - I mean - you know, we were - were told to go but - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 They actually would tell you to go would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
No, I - I think they - they would be careful not to - to talk - you know, if they didn't went it passed on but I mean there were occasions when - I think I told you about I heard my father speak about a builder - did I tell you that 
before? Oh well, this is after the house had just been built and - heard my father say that Mr So and so is as proud as a peacock about this - about the new house. So the next time the builder came in I said to him, I said, father says }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 you\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  as proud as a peacock. And I was told off about this. I said, well you said that. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Did your father overhear you say it do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 He was there. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Can you remember being taught to treat people of one kind differently from another, to 
treat poorer people or better off people any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 I fell there was certain respect for - high class than ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You were brought up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well - I - I've got that feeling there was this - little feeling of cowtowing to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 What sort of people in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 
Well I - I - I think you would - if anybody had a - title for instance, that would be considered - you were different class to them and you would accept it. But the poorer people I mean we were brought up to feel we were all the same. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You mean that you must treat them as equals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you ever remember actually meeting anybody with a title?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Or your father talking about them or doing any business with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Well - no, I - can't really be precise in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 It's more sort of a general impression you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes, I can't give you any precise -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you ever remember coming into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 contact}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  with sort of professional people like a doctor or a solicitor, what their attitude }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3171536\charrsid1014503 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503  them was?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Oh - yes, well I think they - they would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 The same as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, I think they would largely be on a - solicitors, doctors, yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 You think your father would consider them in the same group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Do you think that your mother - I think you said your mother had less confidence as far as social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7434873 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Yes, yes, definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1728290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096523\charrsid1014503 Was that because of her own parents do you think?
